efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N * M) where N is the number of tweets and M is the number of time chunks
space complexity: O(N)
energy implications: LOW 
explanation: The solution uses a HashMap to store tweet counts for each time point. To get the counts for a given frequency and time range, it iterates through the time chunks and sums the counts for each tweet within each chunk. This approach is efficient because it avoids redundant calculations and leverages the fast lookup capabilities of HashMaps.

